import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data, estimator=sum, ci=None)
    chart.axhline(y=data['price'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():.2f}")
    chart.set(xlabel='Company', ylabel='Average Stock Price')
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', hue='symbol', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of stock prices over time for each company?', wrap=True)
    return chart
